description: {"blocks":[{"key":"figva","text":"This protocol describes dissection of the Fallopian tubes in preparation for 10X Visium, 10X Multiomics, pathology review, and biobanking.  The Fallopian tubes have an inner mucosa surrounded by a muscular layer that is coated by serosa.  When sectioning the Fallopian tube the muscule layer may retract or protrude and distort orientation.  This can be addressed by using a stabilizing hand or dissection pins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3ive9","text":"Using a disposable scalpel, divide one Fallopian tube at the cornua and excise mesosalpinx.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cb2vk","text":"Weigh Fallopian tube in a disposable weigh boat on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"emt2h","text":"Place on ice the uterus with the remaining contralateral Fallopian tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4rvpj","text":"Remove the first Fallopian tube from ice and place on a cutting surface.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"920ba","text":"Divide Fallopian tube into four sections: isthmus, ampulla, infundibulum, and fimbriae.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2d94i","text":"Working one section at a time, slice tissue into four sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8jim9","text":"Using disposable weigh boats, weigh each tissue piece.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"54dll","text":"Remove the uterus with the remaining contralateral Fallopian tube from ice and repeat above steps.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
